Stuff for [http://www.ruby-lang.org/ Ruby, an object-oriented scripting language].

* [https://github.com/emacs-tw/awesome-emacs#ruby has package recommendations]
* RubyMode
* EnhancedRubyMode
* GonzuiForEmacs - search source code
* FlymakeRuby - on-the-fly syntax checking
* RubyBlockMode - highlight matching blocks
* RspecMode - navigate to and run specs
* RubyTestMode - run ruby tests
* [[ruby-debug]] - an easier way to debugging in ruby.
* [[ruby-compilation.el]] - run a ruby process in a compilation buffer
* RubyEvalRegion

== Documentation ==
Utilities for consulting the documentation using Ri or other tools.

* RiEl
* [http://www.emacswiki.org/emacs/YARI YARI] (Yet Another Ri Interface)
* LangHelp

== Ruby on Rails ==
Tools specifically used for helping you with developing in [http://rubyonrails.org/ Ruby on Rails].

* RubyOnRails
* [NxhtmlMode nXhtml]

== Using Ruby to extend Emacs ==

* EmacsLispForRuby
* ReLisp (another ruby/emacs bridge)

